// Reactive cells declared at file top level — §6.1 / §7.6.
// MIGRATED S192 (bug-12-vkill stage-2): the legacy file-top BARE-WRITE form
// (`@count = 0` outside any `<program>`/`${}` host) is non-canonical — it parses
// as inert text (the write is silently dropped) so the `${@count}` reads
// resolve to an undeclared cell. The canonical form is a structural declaration
// `<count> = 0` in a default-logic host; under v0.3 a `<program>` body auto-lifts
// bare top-level declarations (§40.8). See E-STATE-UNDECLARED §6.1.1 V-kill.
<program>
    <count> = 0
    <theme> = "light"

    <p>${@theme} / ${@count}</>
</>
